香港的[[裁縫|裁縫]]享譽國際<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attractions-g294217-Activities-c26-Hong_Kong.html |title=Top Attractions in Hong Kong, TripAdvisor |access-date=2021-01-07 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126000126/https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attractions-g294217-Activities-c26-Hong_Kong.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，每年不少[[遊客|遊客]]都會前來度身訂做[[西裝|西裝]]，當中不乏外國政要及名人，包括：[[查理斯王子|查理斯王子]]、[[比爾·克林頓|比爾·克林頓]]、[[小布殊|小布殊]]、[[戴卓爾夫人|戴卓爾夫人]]、[[貝理雅|貝理雅]]、[[鮑勃·霍克|鮑勃·霍克]]、[[奇雲·史柏西|奇雲·史柏西]]、[[波里斯·碧加|波里斯·碧加]]、[[大衛·寶兒|大衛·寶兒]]、[[李察·基爾|李察·基爾]]、[[米高·積遜|米高·積遜]]等等<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tharawat-magazine.com/grow/sams-tailor/|title=Sam’s Tailor: A Cut Above the Competition|publisher=Tharawat Magazine|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107173209/https://www.tharawat-magazine.com/grow/sams-tailor/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theman.in/people/sam-s-tailors-world-s-most-popular-suitmakers.html|title=Sam’s Tailors: World’s most popular suitmakers|publisher=The Man|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109192448/https://www.theman.in/people/sam-s-tailors-world-s-most-popular-suitmakers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/article/401804/roshan-melwani|title=Roshan Melwani|publisher=South China Morning Post|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109100125/https://www.scmp.com/article/401804/roshan-melwani|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/article/487639/sams-tailor-loses-its-iron-lady-matriarch|title=Sam's Tailor loses its 'iron lady' matriarch|publisher=South China Morning Post|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112033735/https://www.scmp.com/article/487639/sams-tailor-loses-its-iron-lady-matriarch|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|date=2013|title=Fodor's Hong Kong: with a Side Trip to Macau|url=http://google.com/books?id=sVWeR1aHGLoC&pg=PT271&lpg=PT271|publisher=Fodor's Travel|pages=271-274|isbn=9780770432829}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pulse.ng/bi/strategy/strategy-the-worlds-most-famous-tailor-has-followed-one-simple-plan-that-has-grown/nq04m1t|title=The world's most famous tailor has followed one simple plan that has grown his tiny Hong Kong shop from a small business into a global brand|publisher=Pulse NG|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2020-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410202245/https://www.pulse.ng/bi/strategy/strategy-the-worlds-most-famous-tailor-has-followed-one-simple-plan-that-has-grown/nq04m1t|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.sg/how-to-be-fashionable-on-a-budget-expert-advice-2018-4|title=The world’s most famous tailor has one simple rule he follows to stay fashionable without emptying the bank account|publisher=Business Insider|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2020-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410200739/https://www.businessinsider.sg/how-to-be-fashionable-on-a-budget-expert-advice-2018-4|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

部分裁縫更加提供24小時內出貨的服務，亦有香港裁縫帶同布料樣本飛到外地為客戶度身，並將完成的西裝以郵遞型式寄到顧客的住址<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/02/fashion/finding-a-custom-tailor-in-hong-kong.html |title=When in Hong Kong ... By KEITH BRADSHER, New York Times, FEB. 1, 2012 |access-date=2021-01-07 |archive-date=2021-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416015307/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/02/fashion/finding-a-custom-tailor-in-hong-kong.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 革沿 ==
香港的裁縫行業可以追溯至20世紀初期的[[上海|上海]]，當時有一班裁縫專門為旅居當地各[[租界|租界]]的外籍人士縫製西裝<ref>{{cite web|url=https://discovery.cathaypacific.com/the-best-hong-kong-tailors/?lang=zh-hans|title=最優秀的香港西裝裁縫|date=2020-02-10|author=Abid Rahman|publisher=Discovery|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108124307/https://discovery.cathaypacific.com/the-best-hong-kong-tailors/?lang=zh-hans|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[國共內戰|國共內戰]]時期，大批師傅南下，帶同他們的技術走難來到香港<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeout.com.hk/hong-kong/hk/%E8%B3%BC%E7%89%A9/%E5%82%B3%E7%B5%B1%E4%B8%8A%E6%B5%B7%E8%A3%81%E7%B8%AB%E5%BA%97%E8%88%87%E6%96%B0%E6%B4%BE%E8%A5%BF%E8%A3%9D%E8%A8%82%E9%80%A0%E5%93%81%E7%89%8C|title=匠人精神：傳統與新派西裝訂造品牌|publisher=Time Out Hong Kong|date=2020-04-20|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124101836/https://www.timeout.com.hk/hong-kong/hk/%E8%B3%BC%E7%89%A9/%E5%82%B3%E7%B5%B1%E4%B8%8A%E6%B5%B7%E8%A3%81%E7%B8%AB%E5%BA%97%E8%88%87%E6%96%B0%E6%B4%BE%E8%A5%BF%E8%A3%9D%E8%A8%82%E9%80%A0%E5%93%81%E7%89%8C|dead-url=no}}</ref>。裁縫師傅當中亦有印度裔人士，香港印度裔商人[[夏利萊|夏利萊]]亦曾經經營裁縫店<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/-/223407|title=An Interview|publisher=HK01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/-/223724|title=An Interview|publisher=HK01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestandnews.com/culture/%E9%80%A0%E5%A4%A9%E8%A1%A3-%E7%82%BA%E9%98%AE%E6%B0%8F%E6%B4%8B%E6%9C%8D%E7%9A%84%E9%98%AE%E5%85%88%E7%94%9F%E5%AF%AB%E4%B8%80%E9%A6%96%E6%AD%8C/|title=Making Perfect Clothes|publisher=The Stand News|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107230836/https://www.thestandnews.com/culture/%E9%80%A0%E5%A4%A9%E8%A1%A3-%E7%82%BA%E9%98%AE%E6%B0%8F%E6%B4%8B%E6%9C%8D%E7%9A%84%E9%98%AE%E5%85%88%E7%94%9F%E5%AF%AB%E4%B8%80%E9%A6%96%E6%AD%8C/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.passiontimes.hk/article/03-02-2018/43847|title=An Interview|publisher=Passion Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427161750/http://www.passiontimes.hk/article/03-02-2018/43847|archive-date=2019-04-27|access-date=2021-01-07|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.mingpao.com/pns/-/article/20170924/s00002/1506187296068|title=A Legacy of More Than 20 Years|publisher=Ming Pao|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411005831/https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%e6%b8%af%e8%81%9e/article/20170924/s00002/1506187296068/%e6%89%8e%e6%a0%b9%e5%bb%bf%e8%bc%89-%e6%95%ac%e6%a5%ad%e8%a3%81%e7%b8%ab%e5%91%8a%e5%88%a5%e4%b8%ad%e7%92%b0%e8%a1%97%e5%b8%82-%e9%9b%a3%e6%8d%a8%e8%a1%97%e5%9d%8a%e6%83%85-%e7%9b%bc%e6%b4%bb%e5%8c%96%e5%be%8c%e9%87%8d%e5%9b%9e%e8%88%8a%e5%9c%b0|archive-date=2020-04-11|access-date=2021-01-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

時至1960年代，香港裁縫業的規模已經超過英國[[薩佛街|薩佛街]]（當時世界公認定制西裝的龍頭）。儘管現成的西裝於1970及80年代開始普及，香港在遊客心目中的地位依然不變<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/travel/activities-and-interests/tailored-tourism-why-getting-a-suit-on-vacation-isnt-a-far-fetched-idea/article34122297/ |title=Tailored tourism: Why getting a suit on vacation isn’t a far-fetched idea, ELLEN HIMELFARB, The Globe and Mail, Feb. 23, 2017 |access-date=2021-01-07 |archive-date=2017-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323142848/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/travel/activities-and-interests/tailored-tourism-why-getting-a-suit-on-vacation-isnt-a-far-fetched-idea/article34122297/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

